# Canvas Interactions

## Plan

- D3 canvas component mounted in a React ref
- Pan (drag background) + zoom (scroll/pinch)
- Tap empty space → node appears at click coordinates
- Auto-edge: nearest existing node connected on creation (Euclidean distance)
- First node → no edge (nothing to connect to)
- Drag a node → repositions it, edges stretch live
- Long-press node + drag outward → rubber-band preview line → release creates new node with explicit edge from source
- Long-press + release on existing node → edge only, no new node
- Long-press + release within 10px of origin → treated as click, no creation
- Long-press threshold: 300ms

## Built

### Stage 1 (2026-03-27)
Full canvas interaction shipped:
- D3 SVG mounted in `useRef`, zoom + pan via D3 zoom behavior
- Click empty space → node at click coords, auto-connect to nearest neighbor
- Drag node → live edge stretch, PATCH on drag end
- Long-press edge-draw mode: rubber-band dashed line from source, release creates node + explicit edge
- All state in React `useState` (no DB yet)

### Post-Stage 2 Polish (2026-03-28)
- Ghost edge on multi-select drag end fixed: canvas click after drag was creating a spurious node. Fixed by checking `selectedNodeIds.size > 0` in click handler and returning early

### Multi-select (2026-03-28)
- Shift+click a node = select entire subtree rooted at that node (BFS via `src/lib/subtree.ts`)
- Dragging a selected node when multiple are selected moves all together, PATCHes all on drag end
- Click empty space clears selection
- `selectedNodeIds: Set<string>` state in `page.tsx`, passed to Canvas as prop
- Selection ring rendered as `circle.select-ring` in D3, opacity toggled by selection state
- Small hint bar at bottom: "N nodes selected · Press Delete to remove"
- `multiDragRef` tracks per-node offset during group drag

### Subtree copy as markdown (2026-04-01)
- `subtreeToMarkdown(nodes, edges, selectedIds, rootId)` added to `src/lib/subtree.ts`: BFS over selected-only edges, depth-tracked, formats as `"  ".repeat(depth) + "- " + text`, skips empty/null text
- `onCopySubtree?` prop added to Canvas; `useEffect` listens for `Cmd/Ctrl+C` when selection is non-empty, fires callback + prevents default
- `handleCopySubtree` in `page.tsx`: detects root (node with no incoming edge from another selected node), calls `subtreeToMarkdown`, writes to `navigator.clipboard`
- `HintBar` component in `page.tsx`: shows node count + char count + "Copy Text" button with 1.5s "Copied!" feedback; replaces old inline hint bar div

### Subtree detach + reattach (2026-04-01)
- HintBar now shows "Detach" button for any selection (renders when onDetach is provided, which is always when selectedNodeIds.size > 0)
- Detach: finds subtree root (selected node with no incoming edge from another selected node), deletes its parent edge optimistically, fires DELETE /api/edges/[id]
- Re-attach: long-press drag from any node, release on existing node within NODE_R + 8 radius → calls onEdgeCreate(sourceId, targetId) instead of creating a new node
- onEdgeCreate in page.tsx: rejects if target already has a parent ("Already has a parent" toast) or would form a cycle ("Would create a cycle" toast); otherwise optimistically adds temp edge → POST /api/edges with color → reconciles with real edge on success, rolls back on failure
- wouldFormCycle(sourceId, targetId, edges) added to src/lib/subtree.ts: BFS from targetId, returns true if sourceId is reachable
- Inline error toast: edgeError state + showEdgeError helper converts canvas coords to screen coords via current transform, renders absolutely-positioned red pill near target node, auto-clears after 2s
- Edge color: POST /api/edges body includes color from sessionColorRef; onSave POST body always sends color and edgeColor (no longer conditional)

## Key Files
- `src/components/Canvas.tsx` — all D3 canvas logic; onEdgeCreate prop + hit detection in drag end
- `src/lib/nearest.ts` — Euclidean nearest-node util
- `src/lib/subtree.ts` — getSubtreeIds, subtreeToMarkdown, wouldFormCycle
- `src/app/page.tsx` — owns node/edge state, HintBar, onEdgeCreate, onDetach, showEdgeError, edgeError toast
- `src/app/api/edges/route.ts` — POST /api/edges
- `src/app/api/edges/[id]/route.ts` — DELETE /api/edges/[id]